An adorable orphaned wombat has formed a very special bond with her surrogate mum – who just happens to be a human.

The helpful wombat named Chloe, who is nine-months-old, follows her zoo keeper Evelyn Weston around Taronga Zoo’s grounds overlooking Sydney Harbour every day.

‘It’s a natural behaviour and something Chloe would be doing with her real mother if she’d survived,’ Evelyn said.

